               <p>516. 
               
                  <persName id="t17791020-39-defend455" type="defendantName">
                     THOMAS
                      TYLER
                  <interp inst="t17791020-39-defend455" type="surname" value="TYLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17791020-39-defend455" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17791020-39-defend455" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , was indicted for <rs id="t17791020-39-off207" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17791020-39-off207" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17791020-39-off207" type="offenceSubcategory" value="bankrupcy"></interp>
               wilfully, fraudulently, and feloniously concealing great part of his personal estate (to more than the value of 20 l.) to which he was intitled before the time of the issuing of a commission of bankrupt against him, to wit, the sum of 61 l. 10 s. which at the time of issuing the commission was due and owing to him, from 
                     <persName id="t17791020-39-person456">
                        Richard
                         Dowding
                     <interp inst="t17791020-39-person456" type="surname" value="Dowding"></interp>
